<br>
My personal quick rule of thumb when looking at weapons, take the Damage multiply by 2.  If it is greater then the delay it is worth equiping until you can find something with more of a difference between 2*Damge and Delay.<br>
<br>
A bigger problem is that after the 12/23 and 11/20 from Tenebrous mountains there are maybe one or two better h2h that are not no drop.  And there are weapons of every other kind with better ratios that can be traded and are more common, which is more then a little unfair considering we are obviously supposed to be primarily h2h fighters. <p>Cheetira Thunderkatt<br>
